[normal]The LCICG brings together the major 
[normal]UK 
[normal]public sector backed organisations that 
[normal]support
[normal] low carbon 
[normal]technology 
[normal]innovation. 
[normal]The LCICG members between them expect to invest in excess of £1billion of public funding in low carbon innovation technologies between 2011-15. 
[normal]The LCICG is not an organisation 
[normal]but
[normal] a group of 
[normal]organisations
[normal] which meet 
[normal]regularly
[normal] 
[normal]and work together to deliver 
[normal]a joint workplan
[normal].  
[normal]The Group 
[normal]is supported by a 
[normal]secretariat (0.5FTE) resourced 
[normal]by
[normal] the 
[normal]D
[normal]epartment of Energy and Climate Change
[normal] (DECC)
[normal].  The LCICG
[normal]’s aim is
[normal] 
[normal]to maximise the impact of UK public sector funding for low carbon technologies, in order to:
[normal]This evidence is
[normal] presented as
[normal] a joint response fro
[normal]m
[normal] the 
[normal]core 
[normal]members of the 
[normal]LCICG
[normal],
[normal] which are the: 
[normal]Department for Business 
[normal]Innovation and Skills
[normal] (BIS)
