[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]48.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]At the EU level, Horizon 2020 has replaced the Framework Programme. Horizon 2020 is intended as a 
[normal]single integrated mechanism for supporting EU research and innovation, 
[normal]and will run from 2014 until 2020. Funding for energy 
[normal]research and innovation
[normal] will be a
[normal]round €1bn a year, 
[normal]more than double
[normal] the amount available previously. Subject to certain conditions, the new mechanism is also open to entities from all over the world, and therefore provides more collaboration opportunities for researchers, scientists and 
[normal]innovative businesses.
[normal]49.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Horizon 2020 presents opportunities for LCICG members to build on the progress made under the Framework Programme - to make greater use of the funding on offer while bringing industry and academia together in productive international
[normal] collaborations
[normal]50.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The UK has been successful in positioning itself at the heart of the EU’s processes for setting energy priorities, under the 
[normal]Communitie
[normal]s
[normal]’
[normal] 
[normal]coordinated technology programme - the Strategic Energy Technology Plan (SET Plan). However, there is 
[normal]scope to do more: in addition to LCICG members collaborating with each other and with private sector partners, they are increasingly seeking to forge international partnerships to pool resources and share risks in taking forward joint programmes. Internati
[normal]onal collaborations help UK companies to gain technical expertise from their foreign counterparts and provide access to new markets.
[normal]51.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]One such example in practice is the ‘BESTF’ ERA-NET 
[normal](Networks Emerging from European Research Area) 
[normal]Plus
[normal], a consortium of 
[normal]eight EU Member States, including the UK, and associated countries. This venture is providing funding and support to collaborative bioenergy projects that demonstrate one or more innovative steps resulting in pre-commercial demonstration. 
[normal]Members of the LC
[normal]ICG are 
[normal]also engaged in ERANETS in Solar and Marine energy technologies
[normal] 
[normal]as well as Industrial Biotechnology and Bioenergy
[normal]52.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
