[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The devolved Governments 
[normal]and Local Enterprise Part
[normal]nership (LEPs) 
[normal]use
[normal] 
[normal]the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) as a springboard to launch and establish low carbon energy innovation programmes
[normal] in assisted areas
[normal].
[normal]54.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The European Commission has identified that a new impetus is needed to join up energy techn
[normal]ology policies across the EU. Implementation plans for 2013-15 under the SET Plan European Industrial Initiatives are to be drawn up to help identify the priority areas for Member State collaboration in the short term. For the longer term, Horizon 2020 - t
[normal]he EU’s new, simplified research, development, demonstration and deployment support programme - includes international cooperation as an important cross-cutting priority. The expectation among LCICG members and beyond is that exploring productive partnersh
[normal]ips and finding common interests with others will in future play a much bigger role in low carbon innovation activity
[normal].
