[normal]79.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 2010 Spending Review announced 
[normal]DECC 
[normal]capital 
[normal]funding of over £200m for low carbon technologies. This included up to £60m for the development of offshore wind manufacturing at port sites. The remaining capi
[normal]tal funding is supporting innovation in low carbon technologies and systems. Using the 
[normal]TINAs, 
[normal]the programme has prioritised key technology families, to inform innovation plans and properly target spending.
