[normal]95.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Scottish Enterprise sees company and sector
[normal] innovation as a key driver of productivity and competitiveness. With our partners, we are taking a more integrated approach to stimulating innovation, knowledge transfer and commercialisation, with a focus on getting more new products and services into gl
[normal]obal markets.
[normal]96.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Scottish Enterprise’s Low Carbon Implementation Plan includes supporting Scottish companies to innovate, diversify into new markets, technologies and supply chains, and to embed low carbon into their business planning.  
[normal]We also invest in key 
[normal]infrastructure such as ITREZ and Scottish Energy Lab as well as providing support, such as 
[normal]grants
[normal],
[normal] for investment in R&amp;D
[normal], innovation and 
[normal] commercialisation.  
[normal]Scottish Government
[normal]97.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The transition to a low carbon economy is one of the Scottish Government’s st
[normal]rategic priorities.  It aims to achieve this by supporting the right innovative low carbon technologies, and funding technological innovation by developing the key technologies for demonstration through refocusing and repriorit
[normal]i
[normal]sing innovation support.
[normal]98.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The
[normal] Scottish Government is establishing new technology hubs and alliances through its partner organisations - to act as focal points for low carbon innovation – including European Structural Funds and overseas R&amp;D investment.
