[normal]Associate Members[bold]101.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]These are organisations that support a more specific set of low carbon technologies and/or have smaller budgets than Core Members to support technology development.  These 
[normal]members choose which of the group’s activities to be involved in.
[normal]The Crown Estate
[normal]102.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Crown Estate manages the seabed out to a distance of 12 nautical miles from the shore and has certain commercial rights beyond that, in particular relating to renewable 
[normal]energy
[normal],
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]with the goal of making a surplus for the benefit of the nation.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] It is a key player in supporting the delivery of a diverse and secure energy supply for the UK, particularly by seeking to successfully exploit the country’s significant offshore win
[normal]d, wave and tidal energy resources. The Crown Estate also has a significant onshore portfolio of which low carbon renewable energy is a part.
[normal]Department for Communities and Local Government
[normal] (DCLG)
[normal]103.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]DCLG has an important part to play in protecting and enhanc
[normal]ing the environment and supporting sustainable economic growth, through its responsibilities for housing, planning and the building regulations.  In particular, Energy Certificates can help the energy efficiency of existing homes, whilst standards are usef
[normal]ul for the energy aspects of new buildings.
[normal]Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (Defra)
[normal]104.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Defra aims to drive sustainable emission reductions in the agriculture, waste and forestry sectors and support the sustainable deployment of low carbon a
[normal]nd renewable energy.  A portfolio of research and delivery programmes sets out to achieve further emissions reductions and better resource efficiency in sectors such as agriculture, food, forestry and waste.
[normal]Department for Transport
[normal] (DfT)
[normal]105.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]DfT is responsibl
[normal]e for overall transport strategy, with a vision for a transport system that is an engine for growth, is greener, safer and improves quality of life.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] In the current parliament, in addition to smaller programmes, DfT is providing over £400m to promote uptak
[normal]e of the next-generation of ultra-low emission vehicle technologies, and has allocated £600m through the Local Sustainable Transport Fund which includes bespoke local sustainable transport projects contributing to economic growth and carbon reduction.
[normal]Mini
[normal]stry of Defence
[normal]106.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The MoD Estate accounts for around 1% of the country’s landmass, and includes nearly 50,000 Service personnel houses.  The Defence Infrastructure Organisation, which manages them, is investing in a £105m three year investment programme of e
[normal]nergy efficiency measures.  Over 80% of electricity demand for the Estate is provided by renewable or CHP suppliers.
[normal]Department of Enterprise, Trade and Industry
[normal] 
[normal]107.
