[normal]ies including security of supply and enhancing sustainability.  Support for energy 
[normal]innovation is channelled through Invest NI, which regularly engages with over 400 businesses, promotes inward investment and has developed a Competence Research Centre for S
[normal]ustainable Energy.
[normal]Ofgem
[normal]108.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Ofgem is the Office of the Gas and Electricity Markets, with a priority for consumer protection through the promotion of competition and regulation of monopoly companies. Low carbon innovation is supported through the £500m Low Car
[normal]bon Networks Fund as well as a new price control regime which puts innovation and efficiency at its core.
[normal]Welsh Government
