[normal] In the US, for example, in 2001 the National 
[normal]Academy of Sciences examined 17 federal R&amp;D programmes in energy efficienc
[normal]y, estimating that the return on the $300m investment was around $30bn. This was attributed almost entirely to the success of 3 of the 17 programmes, illustrating the huge variability in programme returns and lending support to an approach of supporting a 
[normal]range of projects.
